			</div>			<div id="post-689" class="post-689 post type-post status-publish format-aside hentry category-code tag-oauth tag-sfc" itemprop="blogPosts" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/BlogPosting">
				<h2 class="posttitle"><a href="http://ottopress.com/2011/quick-fix-for-people-having-sfc-problems/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Quick fix for people having SFC problems" itemprop="url"><span itemprop="name">Quick fix for people having SFC problems</span></a></h2>
				<div class="postmetadata">October 8, 2011, 4:03 pm <!-- by <span rel="author">Samuel “Otto” Wood</span> --></div>
				<div class="postentry" itemprop="description">
					<p>Didn&#8217;t know about this one, but if you&#8217;re having a problem where the FB login buttons added by SFC don&#8217;t seem to do anything, try this:</p>
<ol>
<li>Go to <a href="https://developers.facebook.com/apps/">https://developers.facebook.com/apps/</a> and click on the App in question.</li>
<li>In the left menu, under Settings, click Advanced and look at the settings in the Migrations section.</li>
<li>Switch the &#8220;Encrypted Access Token&#8221; setting to &#8216;Enabled&#8217;.</li>
</ol>
<p>Might fix the issue.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
				</div>

